    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Valve Installation</title>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To prevent personal injury or death, wear safety glasses with side shields. Limit air pressure to
                    207 kPa (30 psi).
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <para>Clean valve faces and seats with a suitable cleaning solvent to remove all dirt or foreign material. Blow
            dry all new and used components using filtered compressed air.
        </para>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Guides must be clean! Use a valve guide brush to clean guides.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Dry valve guides with filtered compressed air.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate inside diameter of new valve stem seal and inside diameter of valve guide with
                clean engine oil. Install stem seal over valve guide until it stops.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Valve seal will not seat completely over valve guide by hand. Seals can be seated using a suitable
                    deep socket and rubber mallet to provide a positive contact with machined base.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate valve stem with clean engine oil and insert valve into cylinder head.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="e300578" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd08/d0885.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Valve seal, spring, and retainer</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Valve seal</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Valve spring</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Valve retainer</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place valve spring over valve stem seal.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install valve spring retainer on top of spring.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="e300579" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd08/d0886.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Valve retainer keys installation</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Valve retainer key</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Valve spring compressor</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, make sure when the valve spring compressor is released, the inside bead
                    of each valve retainer key locks into the key groove of the valve stem.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Compress valve spring with
                <hotlnk document="eges390_293.xml" xrefid="t390001103">Valve Spring Compressor</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t390001103"/>, install two valve stem keys, and release spring compressor.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">After valve replacement, measure
                <hotlnk document="eges390_291.xml" xrefid="E30005A">valve head recession
                    <xref refid="E30005A"/>
                </hotlnk>
                and compare to specifications.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
